		"description": "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0be19950-7fff-3ec2-605a-eb5181332fa2\">When you cast a spell with a casting time of one action and a single target, you can spend a sorcery point to store it in a melee weapon. You may only have one spell stored this way at a time. When you hit with an attack using the melee weapon, the target takes damage as normal and you can use your reaction to cast the spell on the target of the attack. If you begin a rest with a spell stored this way, it is wasted and lost.</span></p>",
